author: Will Glasgow
title: Tony Abbott and Peta Credlin reunite in Canberra
text:
All things must pass. Alex Ellinghausen Share on twitter Share on Google Plus by Will Glasgow Our former ruling duo reappeared in Parliament House in Canberra on Thursday.
Peta Credlin helped her loyal boss and our former Prime Minister, Tony Abbott , move into his new humble office, which sits halfway to Siberia on the House of Representatives side of the building.
Abbott's new office is down a dead end corridor next to Browyn Bishop , the charmer who reportedly voted against him because she felt badly let down at the end of "Choppergate" . Which cruel bastard made that decision?
Meanwhile, Joe Hockey is leaving the ministerial blue carpet for an office next door to Clive Palmer . But that's only a temporary situation before the Washington solution .
